# voit

**VOIT = Vision / Organize / Implement / Tweak.** Four agents, one memory, one bus,
one review gate. Read your role procedure below, consult voit-memory, act.

## the four roles

- `voit/vision`    - tend the vision on `main`, open slices, review, merge. (the default agent)
- `voit/organize`  - own ONE slice, plan it in voit-memory, dispatch workers. plan-only.
- `voit/implement` - implement ONE task in a worktree, tests green, promote up.
- `voit/tweak`     - unrestricted; tweak anything, anywhere - still review before merge.

Your role is in `.claude/role` (derived from your branch). The write-scope hook
enforces what you may write (`.claude/scope`); `tweak` has no scope and is
unrestricted by design.

## the rest

- how work flows  -> `voit/loop`
- the review gate  -> `voit/review`
- the shared voit-memory -> `voit/memory`
- shared conventions -> `voit/conventions`
- self-audit       -> `voit/dogfood`
- repo health pass -> `voit/doctor`

## rules

- Nothing reaches `main` without passing the review gate (`voit/review`).
- Consult voit-memory first; write back every durable decision, term, and script.
- Organizers never write code; workers stay in their worktree; only tweak is
  unrestricted (and tweak still reviews before merging).
- Additions, not restrictions: the core needs only `git`, `bash`, `python3`; jd is
  the knowledge layer; anything else is optional and must never default-deny.

## commands

`/organize <slice>` · `/dispatch <task>` · `/promote <branch>` · `/tweak <task>` ·
`/dogfood [area]` · `/doctor [area]`.
The bus is `python3 .voit/scripts/bus.py` (register/post/ask/reply/inbox/read/watch/roster/board/gc)
and also ships as the `bus` MCP server (`bus.py mcp`), so every agent shares one
roster and mailbox through `bus_*` tools. CLI and MCP are thin clients that JOIN one
long-lived bus daemon - an `AF_UNIX` socket at `.voitbus.sock`, lazily started by the
first client and namespaced per vision-tree (so projects never cross). Address an
explicit id, `*` to broadcast, or a logical `vision` / `up` / `my-organizer` (the
daemon resolves it from branch lineage). Receiving is always a backgrounded
`watch <self>` (the daemon wakes it on arrival - no poll); questions use `ask`/`reply`
with a correlation token. See `voit/loop`.
